Which of these states is farthest north?
Context: N/A
Options: (A) Rhode Island (B) Louisiana (C) Oklahoma (D) South Carolina
qa_pairs.reasoning_text:
1. Rhode Island is positioned in the northeastern corner of the U.S., closer to Canada than any other listed state, as seen by its northernmost placement on the map.  
2. Louisiana lies far to the south, bordered by the Gulf of Mexico, making it clearly the southernmost of the four options shown.  
3. Oklahoma is located in the central part of the country, situated significantly south of Rhode Island’s latitude, visible by its position relative to the northern border.  
4. South Carolina is positioned just north of Georgia and south of North Carolina, placing it further south than Rhode Island but north of Louisiana.  
5. Comparing all four, Rhode Island’s northernmost location, near the Atlantic coast and just below the Canadian border, confirms it as the farthest north among the choices.  

<final> (A) Rhode Island
